!!! Freshness Tracking Tips

The plugin automatically calculates freshness based on the `bag-roast-date`:

* ''Peak'': 7-21 days after roast - flavors are developed and vibrant
* ''Optimal'': 21-60 days after roast - well-integrated flavors, still excellent
* ''Aging'': 60+ days after roast - past prime but still usable

Different coffees peak at different times:

* Light roasts often need more rest (10-21 days)
* Dark roasts peak earlier (7-14 days)
* Natural/anaerobic processed coffees may age differently

!!! Brewing Parameter Guidelines

Track these key parameters for repeatability:

* ''Dose'': Amount of coffee used (grams)
* ''Yield'': Amount of brewed coffee (grams or ml)
* ''Ratio'': Calculated from dose/yield (e.g., 1:15 = 20g dose, 300g yield)
* ''Water Temperature'': Usually 88-96Â°C depending on roast level
* ''Grind Setting'': Note your grinder's setting for consistency
* ''Brew Time'': Total contact time (varies by method)

!!! Rating System Suggestions

Use a consistent 1-10 scale:

* ''9-10'': Exceptional, memorable cup
* ''7-8'': Great daily drinker, very enjoyable
* ''5-6'': Decent, drinkable but room for improvement
* ''3-4'': Underwhelming, needs adjustment
* ''1-2'': Poor extraction or off flavors

